  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`useEffect` should return nothing or `undefined`. The current implementation of `use-effect` in `react-native` ns doesn't always do that. The following example causes it to return the value in the dependency array:\r\n\r\n`(rn/use-effect #(reanimated/set-shared-value y @scroll-height) [@scroll-height])`",
