    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It seems the implementation in `quo.react/effect!` is much more mature and correct. https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/develop/src/quo/react.cljs#L86\r\n\r\nThe implementation of `react-native.core/use-effect` is simply wrong.\r\n\r\nWe can either:\r\n\r\n1. Fix the existing function in `react-native.core/use-effect`.\r\n2. Move (not copy) the `quo.react/effect!` to `react-native.core` and rename it to `use-effect`.\r\n\r\nThere are only two usages of `react-native.core/use-effect`, so it's quite easy to get it replaced. That's why I prefer option 2, and also because `quo.react/effect!` already works, no need to reinvent the wheel.\r\n\r\nI prefer the second option, but before working on this change, @flexsurfer, could you share your opinion here?\r\n",
